com.solacesystems.jcsmp

Class EndpointProperties

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.solacesystems.jcsmp.EndpointProperties

  • public class EndpointProperties
extends Object
    Endpoint properties used for provisioning durable endpoints, and for provisioning non-durable endpoints created through JCSMPSession.createFlow(XMLMessageListener listener, ConsumerFlowProperties flowProps).

      • setQuota

        public void setQuota(Integer quota)
        Sets the message spool quota for an endpoint. This is the maximum size (in MB) available for storing messages in this spool endpoint. The valid range is 1 through 800000. A value of 0 configures the endpoint to act as a Last-Value-Queue, where the appliance enforces a queue depth of one, and only the most current message is spooled by the endpoint. When a new message is received, the current queued message is automatically deleted from the endpoint and the new message is spooled.

        When used for provisioning:

        • A null value means use the default value.

        Parameters:
        quota - The quota for an endpoint.

      • isRespectsMsgTTL

        public Boolean isRespectsMsgTTL()
        The method returns whether the endpoint respects a message's Time-to-Live (TTL) value. If the value is false, the endpoint ignores a message's TTL value.
        • A null value means use the default value.
        Returns:
        Whether the endpoint respects a message's Time-to-Live value.

      • setRespectsMsgTTL

        public void setRespectsMsgTTL(Boolean respectsMsgTimeToLive)
        Whether the endpoint will respect messages' Time-to-Live values. This property is used when provisioning an endpoint.
        • A null value means use the default value.
        Parameters:
        respectsMsgTimeToLive - Whether the endpoint recognizes messages' Time-to-Live values and removes messages that expire.

      • setDiscardBehavior

        public void setDiscardBehavior(Integer discardBehavior)
        If set, whether to notify sender if a message fails to be enqueued to the endpoint.

        A null value means use the appliance default.

        Parameters:
        discardBehavior - One of DISCARD_NOTIFY_SENDER_OFF, DISCARD_NOTIFY_SENDER_ON, or null for default.
